    {
      "id": "PopularPost192563",
      "post_content": "Pairs surprisingly well with [Enlightened Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Enlightened Tutor). I always assumed that a Counterbalance deck would want the ability to shuffle and peek at the top cards frequently, making any use of Tutor seem ill-advised: what if you need to shuffle it away?  \n  \nNowadays people are doing things like running a single [Moat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Moat). An early e-tutor gets Counterbalance, a later e-tutor can find single copies of unusual CMC spells in your deck. It was hilarious watching someone cast [Ad Nauseam](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ad Nauseam) only to have their Counterbalance opponent calmly tutor for [Karn](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=212632). (I wonder if nowadays this 5cmc slot will be taken by [Norn's Annex](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Norn's Annex)?)  \n  \nA word of caution: Counterbalance doesn't counter copies of spells, meaning it doesn't interact well with Storm cards like [Tendrils of Agony](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tendrils of Agony) or the [Hive Mind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hive Mind) + [Pact of Negation](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pact of Negation) kill.",
      "posted_by": "Salient",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost192563\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Pairs surprisingly well with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Enlightened Tutor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Enlightened Tutor\">Enlightened Tutor</a>. I always assumed that a Counterbalance deck would want the ability to shuffle and peek at the top cards frequently, making any use of Tutor seem ill-advised: what if you need to shuffle it away?<br/><br/>Nowadays people are doing things like running a single <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Moat\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Moat\">Moat</a>. An early e-tutor gets Counterbalance, a later e-tutor can find single copies of unusual CMC spells in your deck. It was hilarious watching someone cast <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ad Nauseam\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ad Nauseam\">Ad Nauseam</a> only to have their Counterbalance opponent calmly tutor for <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardid=\"212632\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=212632\">Karn</a>. (I wonder if nowadays this 5cmc slot will be taken by <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Norn's Annex\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Norn's Annex\">Norn's Annex</a>?)<br/><br/>A word of caution: Counterbalance doesn't counter copies of spells, meaning it doesn't interact well with Storm cards like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tendrils of Agony\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tendrils of Agony\">Tendrils of Agony</a> or the <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Hive Mind\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hive Mind\">Hive Mind</a> + <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Pact of Negation\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pact of Negation\">Pact of Negation</a> kill.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '192563'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy67559\">Salient</span>\r\n                                (8/31/2011 12:31:29 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
